  "texts": [
    "Unlike chatbot versions of ChatGPT and other LLMs used in many research studies, LEAP does not require students to prompt the LLMs for learning.",
    "Instead, specific preprompting is handled by the teacher.",
    "However, thanks to the intuitive structure of LEAP, this process is streamlined and not burdensome for educators, thereby freeing them from several time-consuming yet crucial tasks.",
    "At the same time, it strongly reduces the number of erroneous output and hallucinations because the teacher provides the correct solution to the task, and it does not allow the student to get side tracked as it kindly guides the student back to the task.",
    "It has also the advantage that learners do not need to critically reflect as in a chatbot as the output is aligned with the correct solution."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}